  "doc_id": "36642",
  "text": "• V = The H-D bootstrap test is equivalent to a test based on bootstrapping centered observations in [CITATION_1] . The H-I bootstrap test is nearly equivalent to the \"separate bootstrap plan\" in Zhang and Boos (1993) except that they bootstrapped standardized errors within groups, whereas we do so across groups. If validity of assumption (c) is of concern, resampling should be done within groups, i.e., η jk is resampled from { η jl : l = 1, . . . , n j }.",
